  "name": "Searing Light",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>You shoot a blazing ray of light tinged with holy energy. Make a ranged spell attack. The ray deals 5d6 fire damage. If the target is a fiend or undead, you deal an extra [[/r ((@item.level*2)-1)d6[spirit]]] damage.</p>\n<p>If the light passes through an area of magical darkness or targets a creature affected by magical darkness, <em>searing light</em> attempts to counteract the darkness. If you need to determine whether the light passes through an area of darkness, draw a line between yourself and the spell's target</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The target takes double fire damage, as well as double good damage if a fiend or undead.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target takes full damage</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Heightened (+1)</strong> The fire damage increases by 2d6, and the good damage against fiends and undead increases by 2d6.</p>"
    },
